        <article>
            <h2>How Many Should We Put You Down For?</h2>
            <p><em>Posted by Brian on October 19, 2013 at 3:29 PM</em></p>
            <p>The first big rule in sales is that the person leaves empty-handed, they’re not going to come back. You have to have faith in your product; you believe in what you’re selling to them, but they have to believe it too.</p>
            <blockquote>
                “Never give someone a chance to say no when selling your product.”
            </blockquote>
            <p>One way you can keep a customer from going is to avoid asking questions that have yes or no answers. For instance, if you’re offering a service, instead of asking ‘Are you interested in our 3 month service package?’, try ‘Which of our service plans do you think best fits your needs?’. By assuming the customer wants the service, you shift them into making the same thing, and what you’ve done is you’ve helped them figure out the cost of the service and customization because they wanted it rather than just ‘no’.</p>
            <p><a href="#">25 Comments</a></p>
        </article>

